{
  "texts": [
    "98 reported a ML model based on battery-tocloud to optimize the fast charging strategy, which has proven superior to the state-of-the-art rule-based and model-based strategies in terms of charging rapidity, charging safety, and computational complexity.",
    "99 proposed an adaptive model-based reinforcement learning by utilizing a probabilistic surrogate model of the Gaussian process to describe the degradation, meanwhile optimizing the fast-charging protocols.",
    "In terms of the advancement of new materials, fast charging is highly related to ion diffusion, ionic conductivity, and the electrode-electrolyte interfaces in the devices.",
    "We identify three critical properties across the interfaces in the battery system for selecting the optimal materials to enable fast charging.",
    "As shown in Fig. 4a, the diffusion coefficient (D diff) of metal ions between active particles in the cathode, the ionic conductivity (σ) of the electrolytes, and the charge transfer resistance at the electrode-electrolyte interfaces (R ct) are highly correlated to the ion transport and association of ions and electrons in the cathode, anode, and interfaces of the battery."
  ]
}